Lin via MICA — how related are two CUIs?

1. Go up from both CUIs.
2. Find where they meet. That's MICA.
3. Score it: Lin = 2 × MICA_IC / (IC_first + IC_second)


═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
Pattern 1: Parent-child (one hop apart)
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

    Seizure vs Epilepsy:

                    Epilepsy (IC=6.0)      ← MICA
                        |
                    Seizure (IC=8.5)

    They meet immediately. One hop.

    Lin = 2 × 6.0 / (8.5 + 6.0) = 0.828       HIGH. Very related.


═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
Pattern 2: Siblings (meet in the middle)
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

    RA vs OA left knee:

                    Arthritis (IC=8.4)     ← MICA
                   /         \
                 RA          OA
              (IC=14.6)    (IC=10.3)
                                \
                            OA left knee
                             (IC=14.65)

    RA goes up 1 hop. OA left knee goes up 2 hops. Meet at Arthritis.

    Lin = 2 × 8.4 / (14.6 + 14.65) = 0.574    MODERATE. Same family.


═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
Pattern 3: Unrelated (meet at the top)
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

    Seizure vs Hypertension:

                    Disease (IC=1.5)       ← MICA
                   /           \
            Neurological    Cardiovascular
                 |                |
             Epilepsy        Hypertension
                 |
             Seizure

    Both go all the way up. Only meet at "Disease." Too broad.

    Lin = 0.0                                   ZERO. Not related.


═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
Summary
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

    Meet close (1 hop)     →  specific MICA  →  Lin = 0.8+   →  strong match
    Meet in middle         →  moderate MICA  →  Lin = 0.4-0.7 →  same family
    Meet at the top        →  broad MICA     →  Lin = 0.0     →  not related

    The further up they go to meet, the weaker the relationship.
